"{\"uid\": \"redstate.com-bobhoge-2024-07-28-paris-olympic-organizers-apologize-for-opening-ceremony-fiasco-and-its-as-lame-as-youd-expect-n2177482\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"As we have been reporting, the Paris Olympics opening night ceremony was at various times lewd, insulting, and downright boring.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 128, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(That being said, I will give them some credit: the Eiffel Tower laser show was great, as was Celine Dion's performance.)\", \"from\": 129, \"to\": 250, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 223, \"end\": 234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.521776978153452e-37, \"text\": \"Celine Dion\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The show caused widespread outrage, with much of it directed at a group of performers mocking Leonardo da Vinci's iconic \\\"The Last Supper\\\" painting, and now the organizers are apologizing-sort of.\", \"from\": 252, \"to\": 448, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 346, \"end\": 363, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.530832596618209e-23, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The show's director weaklytried to arguethat it had nothing to do with \\\"The Last Supper\\\":  The ceremony's artistic directorThomas Jollyhad distanced his scene from any \\\"Last Supper\\\" parallels after the ceremony, saying it was meant to celebrate diversity and pay tribute to feasting and French gastronomy.\", \"from\": 449, \"to\": 754, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 736, \"end\": 742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9877777408979335, \"rank\": 0.01236846637695701, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic organizers apologize to anyone who was offended during the opening ceremonies.\", \"from\": 756, \"to\": 842, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not really an apology though, it's just another tiring attempt to say it was about inclusivity.\", \"from\": 843, \"to\": 943, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not inclusive when you mock billions of people's religious beliefs.pic.twitter.com/xM305psf6y  Organizers laughably claimed that it was \\\"clearly\\\" not meant to offend anyone, although, to many viewers, it was \\\"clearly\\\" intended to do just that.\", \"from\": 944, \"to\": 1192, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Clearly there was never an intention to show disrespect to any religious group.\", \"from\": 1194, \"to\": 1274, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On the contrary, I think (with) Thomas Jolly, we really did try to celebrate community tolerance,\\\" Descamps said.\", \"from\": 1275, \"to\": 1388, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1374, \"end\": 1382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Descamps\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Looking at the result of the polls that we shared, we believe that this ambition was achieved.\", \"from\": 1389, \"to\": 1484, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If people have taken any offense we are, of course, really, really sorry.\\\"\", \"from\": 1485, \"to\": 1559, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jolly explained his intentionsto The Associated Press after the ceremony.\", \"from\": 1561, \"to\": 1634, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1598, \"end\": 1614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"score\": 0.9999853350416126, \"rank\": 1.4665173612981988e-05, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"My wish is not to be subversive, nor to mock or to shock,\\\" Jolly said.\", \"from\": 1636, \"to\": 1707, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Most of all, I wanted to send a message of love, a message of inclusion and not at all to divide.\\\"\", \"from\": 1708, \"to\": 1807, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Yeah, sorry, no one believes that claptrap.\", \"from\": 1809, \"to\": 1852, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The show was clearly intended to provoke, and provoke it most certainly did, even in France.\", \"from\": 1853, \"to\": 1945, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1938, \"end\": 1944, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9925488722246781, \"rank\": 0.0062997478877961114, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's Marion Mar\\u00e9chal, a member of the European Parliament:  To all the Christians of the world who are watching the#Paris2024ceremony and felt insulted by this drag queen parody of the Last Supper, know that it is not France that is speaking but a left-wing minority ready for any provocation.#notinmyname\\u00c0 tous les chr\\u00e9tiens du monde\\u2026pic.twitter.com/GusP2TR63u  Reaction to the ceremony came from around the globe:  Da Vinci's painting depicts the moment when Jesus Christ declared that an apostle would betray him.\", \"from\": 1946, \"to\": 2464, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1953, \"end\": 1968, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marion_Mar\\u00e9chal\", \"score\": 0.9999998162447978, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marion Mar\\u00e9chal\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marion_Mar\\u00e9chal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marion_Mar\\u00e9chal\"}, {\"begin\": 1986, \"end\": 2005, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Parliament\", \"score\": 0.9999983960532648, \"rank\": 1.5874721827505916e-06, \"text\": \"European Parliament\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Parliament\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Parliament\"}, {\"begin\": 2019, \"end\": 2029, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.8460454187609896, \"rank\": 0.18195604294987458, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 2166, \"end\": 2172, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9925488722246781, \"rank\": 0.0062997478877961114, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2365, \"end\": 2373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2664726308441283e-29, \"text\": \"Da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 2409, \"end\": 2421, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999610462202504, \"rank\": 3.8955297189134036e-05, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thescene during Friday's ceremonyfeatured DJ and producer Barbara Butch - an LGBTQ+ icon - flanked by drag artists and dancers.\", \"from\": 2465, \"to\": 2592, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2523, \"end\": 2536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"score\": 0.9999897744159937, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barbara Butch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Religious conservatives from around the world decried the segment, with the French Catholic Church's conference of bishops deploring \\\"scenes of derision\\\" that they said made a mockery of Christianity - a sentiment echoed by Russian Foreign Ministry spokesperson Maria Zakharova.\", \"from\": 2594, \"to\": 2872, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2670, \"end\": 2692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church_in_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church_in_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church_in_France\"}, {\"begin\": 2677, \"end\": 2692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999981359906, \"rank\": 1.7974346207008167e-09, \"text\": \"Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 2781, \"end\": 2793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999985051619918, \"rank\": 1.4947848938440048e-06, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 2818, \"end\": 2842, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ministry_of_Foreign_Affairs_(Russia)\", \"score\": 0.999999999875854, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Russian Foreign Ministry\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ministry_of_Foreign_Affairs_(Russia)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ministry_of_Foreign_Affairs_(Russia)\"}, {\"begin\": 2856, \"end\": 2871, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maria_Zakharova\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Maria Zakharova\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maria_Zakharova\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maria_Zakharova\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Anglican Communion in Egypt expressed its \\\"deep regret\\\" Sunday, saying the ceremony could cause the IOC to \\\"lose its distinctive sporting identity and its humanitarian message.\\\"\", \"from\": 2873, \"to\": 3054, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2877, \"end\": 2895, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anglican_Communion\", \"score\": 0.9753107289069748, \"rank\": 0.02531426176428016, \"text\": \"Anglican Communion\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anglican_Communion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anglican_Communion\"}, {\"begin\": 2899, \"end\": 2904, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\", \"score\": 0.9999956191968983, \"rank\": 3.754541511107147e-06, \"text\": \"Egypt\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\"}, {\"begin\": 2977, \"end\": 2980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.878098809738935e-19, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Related:The Backlash Continues: Tech Company Pulls Ads From Olympics As Boycott Movement Grows  House Speaker Mike Johnson Disgusted at 'Shocking and Insulting' Olympics Opener  WATCH: Insane Wokeness Overtakes the Olympics, 'Drag Queens' Mock Christianity in Astonishing Display  The organizers of the event are not sorry, and their claims that they did not want to offend ring hollow.\", \"from\": 3056, \"to\": 3442, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3152, \"end\": 3165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speaker_of_the_United_States_House_of_Representatives\", \"score\": 0.9999999999918145, \"rank\": 7.660981005801426e-12, \"text\": \"House Speaker\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speaker_of_the_United_States_House_of_Representatives\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speaker_of_the_United_States_House_of_Representatives\"}, {\"begin\": 3300, \"end\": 3312, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999985051619918, \"rank\": 1.4947848938440048e-06, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They did exactly what they intended, which was to shove their divisive message down the throats of millions of viewers who wanted to see spectacle, not political posturing.\", \"from\": 3443, \"to\": 3615, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Although viewership waspredicted to be lowfor these games, the opening ceremony drew in an estimated28.6 million sets of eyeballs, which is the most since 2012.\", \"from\": 3616, \"to\": 3776, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The question is: will some of them now turn away?\", \"from\": 3777, \"to\": 3826, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Former Arkansas Governor Mike Huckabee wasn't buying the apology andposted thison Twitter/X Sunday:  \\\"IF\\\" it offended anyone is NOT anapology.\", \"from\": 3828, \"to\": 3970, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3835, \"end\": 3843, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arkansas\", \"score\": 0.9999993244430251, \"rank\": 3.383218330201096e-07, \"text\": \"Arkansas\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arkansas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arkansas\"}, {\"begin\": 3853, \"end\": 3866, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Huckabee\", \"score\": 0.9999999996730367, \"rank\": 3.2697799336342787e-10, \"text\": \"Mike Huckabee\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Huckabee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Huckabee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a declaration that they thought it was fine.\", \"from\": 3971, \"to\": 4020, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This pathetic statement makes it worse.\", \"from\": 4021, \"to\": 4060, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Imagine the backlash if theOlympicshad mocked Mohammed and Islam.\", \"from\": 4061, \"to\": 4126, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mark me down as not impressed with the \\\"apology.\\\"\", \"from\": 4127, \"to\": 4176, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I suspect many feel the same way.\", \"from\": 4178, \"to\": 4211, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bob Hoge-pronounced Hoge like rogue-is a RedState front page contributor and Editor, proud father of four, and long-suffering Bears fan (except for the greatest team ever to exist, the '85 Monsters of the Midway).\", \"from\": 4213, \"to\": 4426, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4254, \"end\": 4262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RedState\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"RedState\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RedState\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RedState\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Come join the party on X@Bob_Hoge_CA.\", \"from\": 4427, \"to\": 4464, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright Redstate.com/Salem Media.\", \"from\": 4466, \"to\": 4501, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All Rights Reserved.\", \"from\": 4502, \"to\": 4522, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Terms under which this service is provided to you.\", \"from\": 4523, \"to\": 4573, \"entities\": []}]}"